  "body": "To close this issue, we'll implement the reorg logic for beacon chain node to process. As beacon chain node subscribes to the incoming main chain block, it should notice when there's a reorg happens in the main chain and reorg the beacon chain accordingly.  \r\n\r\nHere is an example provided in the [spec](https://notes.ethereum.org/SCIg8AH5SA-O4C1G1LYZHQ?view):\r\n```\r\ndef reorg_beacon_chain(main_chain, beacon_chain):\r\n    old_head = beacon_chain[-1]\r\n    while beacon_chain[-1].main_chain_ref not in main_chain:\r\n        beacon_chain.pop()\r\n    queue = [beacon_chain[-1]]\r\n    new_head = beacon_chain[-1]\r\n    while len(queue) > 0:\r\n        b = queue.pop(0)\r\n        for c in get_children(b):\r\n            if c.main_chain_ref in main_chain:\r\n                if get_score(c) > get_score(new_head):\r\n                    new_head = c\r\n                queue.append(c)\r\n    update_head(beacon_chain, old_head, new_head)\r\n```",
